<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="1776" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1776">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.77/202.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-08">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 8, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>In answer to another and insistent request for an answer in the matter of
                            wireless telegraph agreement, Panaman Minister for Foreign Affairs
                            states that he has forwarded to Panaman Minister at Washington all the
                            papers and told him to discuss direct with the Department.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Price</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>